headline.main: Helen Wills Moody, Dominant Champion Who Won 8 Wimbledon Titles, Dies at 92

abstract: Helen Wills Moody, arguably most dominant tennis player of 20th century and first American-born woman to achieve international celebrity as an athlete, dies at 92; career reviewed; photo (L)
snippet: Helen Wills Moody, arguably the most dominant tennis player of the 20th century and the first American-born woman to achieve international celebrity as an athlete, died Thursday at a convalescent home in Carmel, Calif.    She was 92 and had been i...
